queries.prompt: Given a user ID, returns members directly associated with the user as well as members associated with the user via a shared access contact.
Given a a team_id or division_id, returns all members that are commissioners of the divisions that the team is in.

Given a user ID, returns all members associated with user's active season teams.  If include_archived_teams (boolean) parameter is supplied, members associated with archived teams will be returned as well.
Searches the division and subdivision for the members meeting the search criteria.

data.name: division_id
data.prompt: Id of the division and descendants to search

data.name: is_unassigned
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that aren't assigned to a team. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_activated
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that have a user. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_commissioner
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that are or are not a commissioner. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_ownership_pending
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not pending ownership. Not used if blank.

data.name: page_size
data.prompt: The number of items to return for each page. Sending this parameter with the query will enable paging for the returned collection.

data.name: page_number
data.prompt: The number of the page to be returned. This requires that paging be turned on by also providing the page_size parameter.

queries.prompt: Searches the division and subdivision for the members meeting the search criteria. Searches using this endpoint accept additional parameters. You can search for equality by formatting the string as 'operator:equals,value:<SEARCH STRING>'. You can also search inquality by using not_equals as 'operator:not_equals,value:<SEARCH STRING>'. You may search for additional parameters by sending them as an array, for instance: ?birthday[]=operator:less_than,value:2016-02-02&birthday[]=operator:greater_than,value:2010-02-02. Other operators are less_than_or_equal and greater_than_or_equal

data.name: division_id
data.prompt: Id of the division and descendants to search

data.name: id
data.prompt: Id of the member to search

data.name: user_id
data.prompt: Id of the user to search

data.name: is_commissioner
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that are or are not a commissioner. Not used if blank.

data.name: birthday
data.prompt: date - Accepts advanced search operators 'less_than' and 'greater_than'.

data.name: team_id
data.prompt: integer - Find all members in a division with the specified team_id(s).

data.name: is_coach
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not a coach. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_manager
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not a team manager. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_non_player
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not a players. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_owner
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not owners. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_ownership_pending
data.prompt: true/false - Find all members in a division that are or are not pending ownership. Not used if blank.

data.name: gender
data.prompt: Male/Female - Find all members in a division with the specified gender.

data.name: first_name
data.prompt: string - Accepts advanced search operators 'equals', 'contains' and 'starts_with'.

data.name: last_name
data.prompt: string - Accepts advanced search operators 'equals', 'contains' and 'starts_with'.

data.name: email
data.prompt: string - Accepts advanced search operators 'equals', 'contains' and 'starts_with'.

data.name: custom_field
data.prompt: string - Required advanced search parameter of 'id' that should be the id of the custom field to be searched on. Accepts advanced search operators 'equals', 'contains' and 'starts_with'.

data.name: registration_form_id
data.prompt: string - Find all members in a division with the specified registration_form_id.

data.name: registration_form_line_item_id
data.prompt: string - Find all members in a division who have selected the specified registration_form_line_item_id.

data.name: registration_form_line_item_option_id
data.prompt: string - Find all members in a division who have selected a given registration_form_line_item_option_id.

data.name: is_assigned
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that are assigned to a team. Not used if blank.

data.name: is_activated
data.prompt: true/false - For all members in a division that have a user. Not used if blank.

data.name: checkout_type
data.prompt: string - Search for a registration checkout type. Valid values are: "1" - In Progress, "2" - Pay Now, "3" - Installment Plan, "4" - Pay Offline, "5" - No Fees

data.name: signup_status
data.prompt: string - Search for a registration based on it's signup status. Value values are: "authorized" - Authorized, "refunded" - Refunded, "failed" - Failed, "active" - Active, "canceled" - Canceled, "charged_back" - Charged Back, "on_checkout" - On Checkout, "paid" - Paid

data.name: search_subdivisions
data.prompt: true/false - Search all the subdivisions of the division provided. True by default.

data.name: batch_invoice_id
data.prompt: Id of batch invoice to search

data.name: invoice_status
data.prompt: string - Search for all members based on a selected batch_invoice_id invoice status, valid values are: "open", "submitted", "pending", "paid", "canceled"

data.name: pending_assignments
data.prompt: string - Search pending assignments for members. "include", "exclude", "only". "exclude" is the default

data.name: page_number

commands.prompt: Given source_member_ids (array) and a destination_team_id, source members and related member data will be imported to the destination team. Newly created members will be returned.

data.name: send_invites
data.prompt: Whether or not to create and send invitations for each imported member. Valid values are either 'true' or 'false' and will default to 'false'

data.prompt: The id of the member to be deleted, this can either be passed as a comma-delimited list of integers or as an array if the post data is JSON.
